General.Name: HOKKAIDO EL. PWR
General.GicIndustry: Independent Power and Renewable Electricity Producers
General.Description: Hokkaido Electric Power Company, Incorporated generates, transmits, and distributes electricity in Japan. The company undertakes electrical and telecommunication, civil engineering and construction, piping, air-conditioning, water supply and drainage equipment construction, and disaster prevention equipment construction, as well as engages in the manufacture, maintenance, sale, and certification of electric meters. It also engages in energy conservation business; sale of coal ash products and civil engineering and building materials; condominiums and apartments, and parking lot business; and travel, insurance agency, electric pole advertising, auto leasing, and hot bath business. In addition, the company provides general construction consultant services for civil engineering, architecture, electricity, environment, and energy; thermal power generation and contract operation of thermal power plants; and acceptance, storage, and withdrawal of overseas coal, and shipping agency and customs clearance business. Further, it engages in the commissioning and consulting for power generation business and maintenance and management of power generation facilities; meter reading and billing, and energy saving solutions; telecommunication services; and information processing system consulting, development, operation, management, education, sale of information processing equipment and software, internet data center business, and other information processing-related services. The company also provides design, printing, bookbinding, subtitling for broadcasts, sale of novelties, gift products, and daily miscellaneous goods, food, etc.; leasing of LNG fuel receiving facilities; electricity retail; and document management improvement work, confidential disappearance processing, and recycling of confidential documents. Hokkaido Electric Power Company, Incorporated was incorporated in 1951 and is headquartered in Sapporo, Japan.
